{"original": "(CNN) — Hotels and railroad travel go way back."}
{"original": "The relationship worked: Rail travelers needed somewhere to sleep, so railroad companies got into the lodging business."}
{"original": "Though the earliest railroad hotels in the USA were primarily for railway workers, later hotels catered to the lavish lifestyles of the Gilded Age."}
