{"original": "And let's face it, in a capitalist system businesses will always be powerful and influential because they bring the material wealth that everyone depends on. That's why we see cities throwing money and tax breaks at corporations to come move there even when the economic benefits are not really crystal clear. So corporations are by necessity pretty powerful."}
{"original": "Q: What are the potential consequences in America if corporate power continues to grow unchecked?"}
