{"original": "Superfund is the government's long-term program to pay for cleaning them up. There's a good chance you live near one."}
{"original": "There are 1,300 (and counting) such sites, the former homes of nuclear power plants, chemical plants, shipyards. That's how the former site of a plant that allowed chemicals to seep into the groundwater can, years later, be turned into a YMCA. There's been a 20-25% reductions in birth defects among children living near sites."}
{"original": "The US Department of Agriculture (9,100 employees in its Food Safety Inspection Service) and the Food and Drug Administration (18,000 employees) are charged with keeping the food and drug supplies safe. FDA called inspectors back to work as the shutdown dragged on. FSIS inspectors worked through the shutdown. How much arsenic is in your cheese? FDA can tell you."}
{"original": "The FDA issues about 200 citations per week on average to producers of food, drugs and other medical devices."}
{"original": "The USDA food safety service inspects domestic and imported meat, and eggs. According to most recent data (July to December 2018) they rejected an average of 320 shipments per week."}
{"original": "The list goes on if you drill down into the many many government agencies that were either totally shut down or were operating without funds for the past month."}
{"original": "The Internal Revenue Service was gearing up to process tax returns and issue refunds without pay. They also recalled workers who verify incomes and enable mortgage companies to process loans."}
{"original": "Park Rangers had gone back to work without pay to keep National Parks from being overrun with waste and vandalized."}
{"original": "The USDA had employees working on loans for farmers and on government relief from new tariffs resulting from Trump's ongoing trade war."}
{"original": "And there's so much more. The list goes on."}
{"original": "And so does the prospect of not funding those operations again after February 15 if Congress and Trump can't find an agreement he finds acceptable to fund a border wall they don't want to give him."}
