{"original": "The words best Toyota Prius ever might not sound that exciting when gas prices are so low. I might as well sell you about the best winter parka ever in the middle of July, right?"}
{"original": "The new Toyota Prius Prime plug-in hybrid could actually generate some buzz, even now. Sales of plug-in hybrids, while still only about half a percent of all car sales in America are climbing, according to Edmunds.com,"}
{"original": "Plug-in hybrids offer the coolness of hi-tech driving with the security of being able to rely on easily accessible fossil fuels when you need to. And, thanks to more powerful packs, they offer more exciting performance than plug-free hybrids."}
{"original": "The Prius Prime goes about 25 miles before it starts running like a regular Prius hybrid on both gasoline and electricity that it generates itself. And, with those more powerful batteries, the Prius Prime gets an EPA-estimated 54 mpg when driving on gasoline, much better than the competing Chevrolet (GM) Volt's 42 mpg. (Chevy goes more than twice as far on electricity alone, though.)"}
