{"original": "However, the odds of the Democrats retaking the Senate have surged in prediction markets in recent days and weeks -- a point that investors are just awakening to. If Democrats sweep in Georgia, they will effectively control the upper chamber of Congress, with Vice President-elect Kamala Harris casting the deciding vote to break any 50/50 stalemates."}
{"original": "Control of the Senate is a 50/50 chance in either direction, Ed Mills, Washington policy analyst at Raymond James, wrote in a note to clients Monday."}
