{"original": "But Menadim (ph) and other bureaucratic actors may have different views. So I think it's a tough one, but I think they are serious about it."}
{"original": "Even more important, I think, is perhaps the role of the Europeans. As I said, we don't do much trade with Iran. They're sort of persona non grata. But the Europeans have a lot of investment in Iran, have a long history of Iranian relations. And the E.U. has called on Iran to adopt a more aggressive set of rules for inspection. And I think the Europeans have a big and a positive role to play here."}
{"original": "SHIELDS: Hey, Jim Walsh, thank you very much for being with us. It's been enormously helpful."}
