{"original": "How much will whole life insurance set you back? While rates vary among insurers, based on a recent search at Top Whole Life, a 30-year-old woman in excellent health could qualify for $250,000 in whole life insurance for about $189 per month. Meanwhile, prices surge to over $373 per month for twice the coverage."}
