{"original": "Ten years after getting their degrees, more than 10% of male graduates from Cambridge, Oxford and the London School of Economics were earning more than £100,000 ($142,000) a year. And the London School of Economics was also the only institution where more than 10% of female graduates were making more than £100,000 after 10 years."}
