{"original": "According to the Office of the US Trade Representative, Mexico is the third-largest US goods trading partner, with more than $296 billion in imports in 2015."}
{"original": "Based on current trade flows, a 20% tariff would effectively impose a $59.2 billion tax on US consumers who purchase Mexican imports. That means that billions of dollars' worth of Mexican fruits, vegetables, beer, minerals, equipment and cars would all be 20% more expensive to US consumers."}
