{"original": "Professor Shambaugh, thanks for joining us. The surveillance flights, the U.S. will say in the negotiation, they'll continue. The Chinese will say, we don't want them. What's going to happen?"}
{"original": "PROFESSOR DAVID SHAMBAUGH, GEORGE WASHINGTON UNIVERSITY: Well, that's going to be the deadlock, and the Chinese well may say: You stop the flights, or you won't get your plane back. That would be one choice I suspect the Washington is going to have to face. But of course, we're going to continue with them. The question is, how far offshore an whether in fact, we escort them with our own fighters."}
