{"original": "(CNN) Polls show more and more Americans are saying they will get the Covid-19 vaccine when it's their turn. That's good news. But skepticism, conspiracy theories and misinformation are still rampant, making it unclear just how much longer we'll be living amidst a viral pandemic and all that comes with it. This week, I talk to Dr. Kent Sepkowitz, a physician at Memorial Sloan Kettering, and Tom Nichols, author of Our Own Worst Enemy, to find out what comes next for America and the vaccine. But first, Sepkowitz writes our CNN op-ed. - SE Cupp"}
