{"original": "So if you don't file your 2014 return by April 17 this year, the US Treasury gets to keep any money you're owed."}
{"original": "The IRS estimates about 1 million people didn't file their 2014 returns and that collectively the group is owed $1.1 billion in back refunds. The estimated median refund is just shy of $850."}
{"original": "Texas, California, Florida and New York are the states with the greatest number of people who didn't file their federal returns in 2014, according to the IRS."}
